    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@rschumi0 I hope it is consistent: `T[3]` is always an array of size 3 with inner type `T`, regardless of what `T` is (it can be another array, a struct or a value type). If you have a variable `x` of type `T[3]`, then `x[2]` is always of type `T`, regardless of what `T` is.",
